rComments: Course was supposed to be super boring and dry but ended up being super interesting because of her. Explains concepts super well. Very approachable in office hours and they're always filled. Tests not too hard. Pretty sure she bell curves too. 10/10 would recommend

Really good at explaining. Hated linear algebra after i had to drop 223 and retake in the summer. Wasn't looking forward to taking 224. Surprisingly, ended up developing a love for linear algebra after this course. Could've gotten a better grade but bombed the second test. So far my favourite math prof at UTM!
